00137 bool
00138 SgAsmLEFileHeader::is_LE(SgAsmGenericFile *file)
00139 {
00140     /* Turn off byte reference tracking for the duration of this function. We don't want our testing the file contents to
00141      * affect the list of bytes that we've already referenced or which we might reference later. */
00142     bool was_tracking = file->get_tracking_references();
00143     file->set_tracking_references(false);
00144 
00145     try {
00146         /* Check DOS File Header magic number at beginning of the file */
00147         unsigned char dos_magic[2];
00148         file->read_content(0, dos_magic, sizeof dos_magic);
00149         if ('M'!=dos_magic[0] || 'Z'!=dos_magic[1])
00150             throw 1;
00151 
00152         /* Read four-byte offset of potential LE/LX File Header at offset 0x3c */
00153         uint32_t lfanew_disk;
00154         file->read_content(0x3c, &lfanew_disk, sizeof lfanew_disk);
00155         rose_addr_t le_offset = le_to_host(lfanew_disk);
00156         
00157         /* Look for the LE/LX File Header magic number */
00158         unsigned char le_magic[4];
00159         file->read_content(le_offset, le_magic, sizeof le_magic);
00160         if ('L'!=le_magic[0] || ('E'!=le_magic[1] && 'X'!=le_magic[1]))
00161             throw 1;
00162     } catch (...) {
00163         file->set_tracking_references(was_tracking);
00164         return false;
00165     }
00166     
00167     file->set_tracking_references(was_tracking);
00168     return true;
00169 }

00669 /* Writes the section table back to disk along with each of the sections. */
00670 void
00671 SgAsmLESectionTable::unparse(std::ostream &f) const
00672 {
00673     SgAsmLEFileHeader *fhdr = dynamic_cast<SgAsmLEFileHeader*>(get_header());
00674     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00675     SgAsmGenericSectionPtrList sections = fhdr->get_sections()->get_sections();
00676 
00677     for (size_t i = 0; i < sections.size(); i++) {
00678         if (sections[i]->get_id() >= 0) {
00679             SgAsmLESection *section = dynamic_cast<SgAsmLESection*>(sections[i]);
00680 
00681             /* Write the table entry */
00682             ROSE_ASSERT(section->get_id()>0); /*ID's are 1-origin in LE*/
00683             size_t slot = section->get_id()-1;
00684             SgAsmLESectionTableEntry *shdr = section->get_st_entry();
00685             SgAsmLESectionTableEntry::LESectionTableEntry_disk disk;
00686             shdr->encode(get_header()->get_sex(), &disk);
00687             write(f, slot*sizeof(disk), sizeof disk, &disk);
00688 
00689             /* Write the section */
00690             section->unparse(f);
00691         }
00692     }
00693 }

00709 // LE/LX Resident and Non-Resident Name Tables
00711 
00712 /* Constructor assumes SgAsmGenericSection is zero bytes long so far */
00713 void
00714 SgAsmLENameTable::ctor(rose_addr_t offset)
00715 {
00716     set_offset(offset);
00717     set_size(0);
00718     grab_content();
00719 
00720     SgAsmLEFileHeader *fhdr = dynamic_cast<SgAsmLEFileHeader*>(get_header());
00721     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00722 
00723     set_synthesized(true);
00724     char section_name[64];
00725     sprintf(section_name, "%s Name Table", fhdr->format_name());
00726     set_name(new SgAsmBasicString(section_name));
00727     set_purpose(SP_HEADER);
00728 
00729     /* Resident exported procedure names, until we hit a zero length name. The first name
00730      * is for the library itself and the corresponding ordinal has no meaning. */
00731     rose_addr_t at = 0;
00732     while (1) {
00733         extend(1);
00734         unsigned char byte;
00735         read_content_local(at++, &byte, 1);
00736         size_t length = byte;
00737         if (0==length) break;
00738 
00739         extend(length);
00740         char *buf = new char[length];
00741         read_content_local(at, buf, length);
00742         p_names.push_back(std::string(buf, length));
00743         delete[] buf;
00744         at += length;
00745 
00746         extend(2);
00747         uint16_t u16_disk;
00748         read_content_local(at, &u16_disk, 2);
00749         p_ordinals.push_back(le_to_host(u16_disk));
00750         at += 2;
00751     }
00752 }
00753 
00754 /* Writes the section back to disk. */
00755 void
00756 SgAsmLENameTable::unparse(std::ostream &f) const
00757 {
00758     rose_addr_t spos=0; /*section offset*/
00759     ROSE_ASSERT(p_names.size() == p_ordinals.size());
00760     for (size_t i = 0; i < p_names.size(); i++) {
00761         /* Name length */
00762         ROSE_ASSERT(p_names[i].size() <= 0xff);
00763         unsigned char len = p_names[i].size();
00764         spos = write(f, spos, len);
00765 
00766         /* Name */
00767         spos = write(f, spos, p_names[i]);
00768 
00769         /* Ordinal */
00770         ROSE_ASSERT(p_ordinals[i] <= 0xffff);
00771         uint16_t ordinal_le;
00772         host_to_le(p_ordinals[i], &ordinal_le);
00773         spos = write(f, spos, sizeof ordinal_le, &ordinal_le);
00774     }
00775     
00776     /* Zero-terminated */
00777     write(f, spos, '\0');
00778 }

00816 /* Write the entry information back to the disk at the specified section and section offset, returning the new section offset. */
00817 rose_addr_t
00818 SgAsmLEEntryPoint::unparse(std::ostream &f, ByteOrder sex, const SgAsmGenericSection *section, rose_addr_t spos) const
00819 {
00820     if (0==(p_flags & 0x01)) {
00821         /* Empty entry; write only the flag byte */
00822         uint8_t byte;
00823         host_to_disk(sex, p_flags, &byte);
00824         spos = section->write(f, spos, byte);
00825     } else {
00826         /* Non-empty entry */
00827         LEEntryPoint_disk disk;
00828         host_to_disk(sex, p_flags,        &(disk.flags));
00829         host_to_disk(sex, p_objnum,       &(disk.objnum));
00830         host_to_disk(sex, p_entry_type,   &(disk.entry_type));
00831         host_to_disk(sex, p_entry_offset, &(disk.entry_offset));
00832         host_to_disk(sex, p_res1,         &(disk.res1));
00833         spos = section->write(f, spos, sizeof disk, &disk);
00834     }
00835     return spos;
00836 }

00868 /* Constructor. We don't know the size of the LE Entry table until after reading the first byte. Therefore the SgAsmGenericSection is
00869  * created with an initial size of zero. */
00870 void
00871 SgAsmLEEntryTable::ctor(rose_addr_t offset)
00872 {
00873     set_offset(offset);
00874     set_size(0);
00875     grab_content();
00876 
00877     SgAsmLEFileHeader *fhdr = dynamic_cast<SgAsmLEFileHeader*>(get_header());
00878     ROSE_ASSERT(fhdr!=NULL);
00879 
00880     set_synthesized(true);
00881     char section_name[64];
00882     sprintf(section_name, "%s Entry Table", fhdr->format_name());
00883     set_name(new SgAsmBasicString(section_name));
00884     set_purpose(SP_HEADER);
00885 
00886     ROSE_ASSERT(0 == get_size());
00887 
00888     if (FAMILY_LX == fhdr->get_exec_format()->get_family()) {
00889         /* FIXME: LX Entry tables have a different format than LE (they are similar to NE Entry Tables). See
00890          *        http://members.rediff.com/pguptaji/executable.htm (among others) for the format. We don't parse them
00891          *        at this time since it's not a Windows format and we leave the section size at zero to make this more
00892          *        obvious. */
00893         return;
00894     }
00895 
00896     rose_addr_t at = 0;
00897     extend(1);
00898     unsigned char byte;
00899     read_content_local(at++, &byte, 1);
00900     size_t nentries = byte;
00901     for (size_t i = 0; i < nentries; i++) {
00902         extend(1);
00903         uint8_t flags;
00904         read_content_local(at, &flags, 1);
00905         if (flags & 0x01) {
00906             extend(sizeof(SgAsmLEEntryPoint::LEEntryPoint_disk)-1);
00907             SgAsmLEEntryPoint::LEEntryPoint_disk disk;
00908             read_content_local(at, &disk, sizeof disk);
00909             p_entries.push_back(new SgAsmLEEntryPoint(fhdr->get_sex(), &disk));
00910         } else {
00911             p_entries.push_back(new SgAsmLEEntryPoint(fhdr->get_sex(), flags));
00912         }
00913     }
00914 }

00920     rose_addr_t spos=0; /*section offset*/

00922     uint8_t byte = p_entries.size();

00926     for (size_t i = 0; i < p_entries.size(); i++) {
